---
<section id="faq">
    <div class="wrap">
        <div class="s-head" data-reveal="up">
            <span class="t-sm">FAQ</span>
            <h2 class="t-h2" style="margin-top:14px;margin-bottom:16px">Questions We Hear<br/><em>Every Day.</em></h2>
            <p class="t-body">Everything you need to know before you book — answered honestly.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-wrap" data-reveal="up" style="transition-delay:100ms">
            <div class="faq-item open">
                <button class="faq-q">How early should I book my move? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
                <div class="faq-a">We recommend 7–14 days in advance. If your move date is a weekend or during October–February or April–June peak season, 2–3 weeks is safer. For genuine emergencies, we do our best within 48 hours — especially for local city moves.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <button class="faq-q">Are my goods insured during transport? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
                <div class="faq-a">Every move includes basic transit insurance at no extra charge. For electronics, antiques, jewellery, and vehicles, we offer comprehensive coverage. We explain all options clearly before you confirm — nothing is hidden in the fine print.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <button class="faq-q">Do you use your own vehicles or outsource to third parties? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
                <div class="faq-a">We own our entire fleet. Every truck that carries your belongings belongs to PackersHub and is GPS-tracked. We do not use sub-contractors or third-party drivers. This is non-negotiable for us — because accountability requires ownership.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <button class="faq-q">Can I track my shipment in real time? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
                <div class="faq-a">Yes. As soon as your goods are loaded and in transit, we share a live GPS tracking link via WhatsApp. You can see exactly where your truck is at any time. No more "where is my stuff" anxiety.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <button class="faq-q">What cities do you serve? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
                <div class="faq-a">75 major cities across Andhra Pradesh (20), Telangana (14), Tamil Nadu (16), Karnataka (15), and Kerala (10). For specific routes and cities, see our Locations section above or WhatsApp us directly.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <button class="faq-q">How is the final price calculated? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
                <div class="faq-a">Pricing depends on distance, volume of goods, floor access at both locations, date of move, and any special items (car, piano, antiques). After a free survey (video or on-site), we give you a detailed written quote. The number we quote is the number you pay — no additions at delivery.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <button class="faq-q">What if something gets damaged? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
                <div class="faq-a">Our damage rate is under 0.1%. In the rare event of damage, our claims process is straightforward. Insured items are repaired or replaced promptly. We take full accountability — because our reputation depends on it.</div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<style>
    .faq-wrap { max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; }
    .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-border); }
    .faq-q {
        width: 100%; text-align: left; padding: 22px 0;
        display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 20px;
        font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--c-ink);
        cursor: pointer; background: none; border: none;
        transition: color var(--dur-fast);
    }
    .faq-q:hover { color: var(--c-brand); }
    .faq-icon {
        width: 28px; height: 28px; border-radius: 50%;
        border: 1.5px solid var(--c-border);
        display: grid; place-items: center; flex-shrink: 0;
        font-size: 16px; color: var(--c-brand);
        transition: all var(--dur-base) var(--ease-spring);
    }
    .faq-item.open .faq-icon { transform: rotate(45deg); background: var(--c-brand); color: #fff; border-color: var(--c-brand); }
    .faq-a {
        font-size: 15px; color: var(--c-muted); line-height: 1.75;
        max-height: 0; overflow: hidden;
        transition: max-height .5s var(--ease-expo), padding .4s;
        padding-bottom: 0;
    }
    .faq-item.open .faq-a { max-height: 300px; padding-bottom: 22px; }
</style>

<script>
    document.querySelectorAll('.faq-q').forEach(btn => {
        btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
            const item = btn.parentElement;
            const isOpen = item.classList.contains('open');
            
            // Close others
            document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item').forEach(i => i.classList.remove('open'));
            
            if (!isOpen) {
                item.classList.add('open');
            }
        });
    });
</script>
